        "is_accepted": true,
        "last_activity_date": 1659381169,
        "creation_date": 1659381169,
        "body": "<p><code>iterator()<\/code> returns an object that implements the Iterator interface. This <em>can<\/em> be accomplished in constant time, of course.<\/p>\n<p>E. g. the iterator might manage a pointer to the current element. At the beginning this pointer might be <code>null<\/code>, so that the first call of <code>hasNext()<\/code> would have to walk down the tree to the first element, which should have a complexity of O(log n).<\/p>\n",
